page.title: 15Boys Football In Woodlesford
page.content: The Rothwell Juniors play at Woodlesford park,they have teams from 7 to 16 years old.Dominic played for the Rothwell Juniors when he was under 10.When they needed a new goalkeeper in 1983 I began playing for them. We go training every Wednesday, we start at 6-0-clock. Normally we start by jogging around the football field, then we do some press-ups.After that we play football. This year Rothwell Juniors under 11's have had a successful season,we have come runners up in the league and the Charles Rice cup.This seasons strip is red with two white stripes down each side and a black stripe down the middle of the white stripe. .
